   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Climate Action with Farmers in Rwanda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GCS has been carrying out this project since 2015 to support self-reliance of the vulnerable people in Nyarubaka Sector. However, climate change creates enormous challenges for those people&apos;s everyday lives heavily dependent on small-scale agriculture. To overcome these challenges, GCS will start &apos;climate-smart agriculture&apos; skills training program for farmers in Nyarubaka. This program will equip the farmers with adaptive capacity to climate change and pave the way to realize self-reliance.</narrative>
  </description>
